## Website: home.mypetdex.app
- Hosted on Vercel, connected to `master` branch
- Static HTML files: `privacy.html`, `terms.html`
- Domain: `home.mypetdex.app`
- App Store link: `https://apps.apple.com/app/mypetdex/id6772248051`
- **No API keys on the website** — it is purely static HTML/CSS/JS
- Never add server-side code or environment variables to the website

---

## App Architecture

### Auth flow:
1. User opens app → checks Firebase Auth state
2. Not logged in → `/(auth)/sign-in.tsx`
3. Logged in but onboarding not complete → `/(auth)/onboarding.tsx`
4. Fully set up → `/(tabs)/` main app

### Navigation (Expo Router file-based):
- `/(tabs)/index.tsx` — Home screen
- `/(tabs)/explore.tsx` — Find services + adopt pets
- `/(tabs)/shopping.tsx` — Pet shop
- `/(tabs)/ai.tsx` — MyPetDex Assistant (AI chat)
- `/(tabs)/me.tsx` — Profile, settings, feedback
- `/pet/[id].tsx` — Pet detail page
- `/pet/add.tsx` — Add new pet

### Key files:
- `MyPetDex/lib/firebase.ts` — All Firebase initialization + helpers
- `MyPetDex/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` — Auth state, Google/Apple sign-in logic
- `MyPetDex/app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx` — Tab bar configuration
- `functions/index.js` — All Cloud Functions

---

## Code Conventions
- Use `WebBrowser.openBrowserAsync()` for Privacy Policy, Terms — never `Linking.openURL` for web pages
- Use `Linking.openURL` only for App Store links
- All feedback goes through `callFunction("sendFeedback")` — never `mailto:`
- Photo uploads use `XMLHttpRequest` blob method — never `fetch().blob()` (broken in Expo's fetch)
- Never use `expo-file-system` for uploads
- Keyboard handling: wrap forms in `KeyboardAvoidingView behavior="padding"` on iOS
- Clear search state when user leaves a search screen (`useFocusEffect` or on unmount)
- Text strings must always be inside `<Text>` components — never render raw strings in `<View>`
- Use `Boolean(value)` or `value != null` checks instead of `&&` with numbers/strings to avoid rendering `0` or `""` as text

